Explanation:

We use a dynamic programming approach to solve the problem. We create a 2D array (dp) with dimensions (m+1)x(n+1), where m is the length of the starting string and n is the length of the ending string. We iterate through the strings and update the dp array accordingly. If the characters at the current positions in the strings are equal, we update the corresponding cell in the dp array with the value from the cell diagonally above and to the left. If the characters are 'X' in either string, we update the cell with the value from the cell directly above. Otherwise, we update the cell with the value from the cell directly to the left. Finally, we return the value at the bottom-right cell of the dp array, which indicates if a sequence of moves can convert the starting string to the ending string.

